HEADWORD: Prenotion
<hw>Pre*no"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praenotio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>pr⟦eacute⟧notion</ets>. See
<er>Prenostic</er>.]</ety> <def>A notice or notion which precedes
something else in time; previous notion or thought; foreknowledge.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

